CNCP v1 23287
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5660: \"Hydration node mismatch\" in very specific template structure",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:30.610445+00:00",
  "text": "\"Hydration node mismatch\" in very specific template structure\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.31\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[github.com](https://github.com/filipsobol/hydration-mismatch-error)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Clone reproduction repository and install dependencies.\r\n2. Run the `dev` command and open `localhost:3000`.\r\n3. Open the browser console to see the error caused by the `src/App.vue` file.\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nNo errors :)\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\"Hydration node mismatch\"  error\r\n\r\nThe [Vue SFC Playground result](https://sfc.vuejs.org/#) shows that the component with this particular structure is parsed into a single `createStaticVNode`, which results in a hydration mismatch. Even minimal change to the template creates multiple `createElementVNode` and `createTextVNode` and fixes the issue.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: ssr",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
